Ejercicio 1 PYTHON

a)

import sympy as sp
X = sp.var('x')
from sympy.solvers.inequalities import solve_univariate_inequality
expr=abs(X-1)
print(solve_univariate_inequality(expr < 3,X))
## (-2 < x) & (x < 4)

b)

import sympy as sp
X = sp.var('x')
from sympy.solvers.inequalities import solve_univariate_inequality
expr=abs(2-3*X)
print(solve_univariate_inequality(expr < 1,X))
## (1/3 < x) & (x < 1)

c)

Ejercicio 2 PYTHON

import sympy as sp
X = sp.var('x')
from sympy.solvers.inequalities import solve_univariate_inequality
expr=abs(5-(1/X))
print(solve_univariate_inequality(expr < 1,X))
## (1/6 < x) & (x < 1/4)

b)

import sympy as sp
X = sp.var('x')
from sympy.solvers.inequalities import solve_univariate_inequality
expr=abs(X**2 - 2)
print(solve_univariate_inequality(expr <= 2,X))
## (-2 <= x) & (x <= 2)

Ejercicio 3 PYTHON

import sympy as sp
X = sp.var('x')
from sympy.solvers.inequalities import solve_univariate_inequality
expr=abs(X + 2) - abs(X-1)
print(solve_univariate_inequality(expr > 0,X))
## (-1/2 < x) & (x < oo)

Ejercicio 4 PYTHON

from sympy import *
from sympy.plotting import plot

x = symbols('x')
p1 = plot_implicit(x**2-12<3*x, (x,-5.,6.), line_color='c')

w1=solve_univariate_inequality(x**2-12<3*x,x)
print(w1)
## (x < 3/2 + sqrt(57)/2) & (3/2 - sqrt(57)/2 < x)
p2= plot_implicit(x<x**2-12, (x,-5.,6.), line_color='y')

w2=solve_univariate_inequality((x<x**2-12), x)
print(w2)
## ((-oo < x) & (x < -3)) | ((4 < x) & (x < oo))

Ejercicio 5 PYTHON

from sympy import *
from sympy.plotting import plot

x = symbols('x')
p = plot_implicit(abs(x-3)-1/3<0)

w=solve_univariate_inequality(abs(x-3)-1/3<0,x)
print(w)
## (2.66666666666667 < x) & (x < 3.33333333333333)

Ejercicio 7 PYTHON

a)

import sympy as sp
X = sp.var('x')
from sympy.solvers.inequalities import solve_univariate_inequality
expr=abs(x**2-3)
print(solve_univariate_inequality(expr > 1,X))
## ((-oo < x) & (x < -2)) | ((2 < x) & (x < oo)) | ((x < sqrt(2)) & (-sqrt(2) < x))

b)

import sympy as sp
X = sp.var('x')
from sympy.solvers.inequalities import solve_univariate_inequality
expr=abs(X**2 - X + 1)
print(solve_univariate_inequality(expr > 1,X))
## ((-oo < x) & (x < 0)) | ((1 < x) & (x < oo))

from sympy.plotting import plot

# c)

from sympy import symbols
from sympy.plotting import plot
scal = 3840/2400
a = 4.05
x = symbols('x')
y = symbols('y')
plot_implicit(Eq(x**2/4+y**2/9,1), x_var=(x,-a*scal,a*scal), y_var=(y,-a,a))
## <sympy.plotting.plot.Plot object at 0x000000002E55EB38>
